---
/**
 * * Privacy Policy Section
 */
import profileImage from "@assets/images/proj.webp";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";

const blocks = [
  {
    title: "Privacy Policy",
    image: profileImage,
    // Using backticks allows for multi-line text
    text: `
      Privacy Policy - Neorama
      Last updated: 22.3.2026

      Neorama (“Neorama”, “we”, “us”, or “our”) respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal data. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, store, and otherwise process personal data when you visit our website, contact us, submit information through our forms, or otherwise interact with us online. This Policy is intended to provide the information required under the General Data Protection Regulation (Regulation (EU) 2016/679 - GDPR) and applicable Greek data protection law.

      1. Data Controller
      The controller responsible for the processing of personal data through this website is:
      Neorama Estates IKE
      Registered address: Fanariou 22, Kalamaria, Greece
      Email: orri@neorama.org

      2. Personal Data We May Collect
      Depending on how you interact with our website, we may collect and process the following categories of personal data:
      • Contact and identification data: Name, email, phone number, country, company, job title.
      • Communications data: Content of messages, inquiries, meeting requests.
      • Technical and usage data: IP address, browser type, device type, operating system.
      • Cookie and tracker-related data: Information collected through pixels and tracking mechanisms.

      3. How We Collect Personal Data
      We collect data directly from you (forms/communications), automatically via cookies, and from service providers helping us operate the website.

      4. Purposes of Processing and Legal Bases
      We process data to respond to inquiries, operate the website, improve user experience, send marketing updates (with consent), and comply with legal obligations.

      5. Whether You Must Provide the Data
      Providing data is voluntary, but refusal may prevent us from responding to inquiries or providing requested information.

      6. Recipients of Personal Data
      We may share data with hosting providers, CRM platforms, analytics services, legal advisors, or public authorities where required by law.

      7. International Transfers
      Data is primarily processed in the EEA. Transfers outside the EEA occur only under lawful mechanisms like Standard Contractual Clauses.

      8. Data Retention
      We retain data only as long as necessary for the purposes outlined or as required by Greek law.

      9. Cookies and Trackers
      We use cookies for site functionality and analytics. You can manage these through your browser or our consent banner.

      10. Your Rights
      Under GDPR, you have the right to access, rectify, erase, or object to the processing of your data. To exercise these rights, contact: orri@neorama.org.

      11. Data Security
      We implement technical measures to protect your data, though no internet transmission is 100% secure.

      12. Contact Us
      Neorama Estates IKE
      Email: orri@neorama.org
    `
  },
];
---

<section id="policy" class="site-container scroll-mt-2 py-4 md:py-8">
  <div class="space-y-6 md:space-y-4">
    {blocks.map(block => (
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-1 gap-6 lg:gap-12 items-start">
        <div>
          <h3 class="h2 mb-6">{block.title}</h3>
          
          <div class="bg-base-100 p-8 lg:p-10 lg:text-lg shadow-sm border border-base-200 rounded-sm">
            {block.text.split('\n').map((line) => {
              const trimmedLine = line.trim();
              
              // Skip empty lines
              if (!trimmedLine) return <br />;

              // Regex to check if the line starts with a number followed by a dot (e.g., "1. ")
              const isSectionTitle = /^\d+\./.test(trimmedLine);

              return (
                <p class={`mb-4 whitespace-pre-line ${isSectionTitle ? 'font-bold text-xl mt-6' : ''}`}>
                  {trimmedLine}
                </p>
              );
            })}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>
</section>